WEBVTT

00:05.614 --> 00:06.658
What happened to this country?

00:10.097 --> 00:11.098
Bravo.

00:28.898 --> 00:31.031
<i>It's a really weird time
in the household</i>

00:31.074 --> 00:35.078
because Colin Robinson
is no longer with us.

00:35.122 --> 00:37.080
I mean, vampires are
no strangers to death.

00:37.124 --> 00:39.648
They deal with it every day
with the people that they kill.

00:39.691 --> 00:41.563
But when they lose
one of their own,

00:41.606 --> 00:43.173
they just don't know
how to deal with it.

00:43.217 --> 00:45.088
<i>I mean, their only
funeral-type tradition</i>

00:45.132 --> 00:46.872
<i>is that they get
a new portrait made</i>

00:46.916 --> 00:48.483
<i>with all of them except for
the newly deceased,</i>

00:48.526 --> 00:49.962
<i>and I don't think that's
a really healthy way</i>

00:50.006 --> 00:52.095
of dealing with the loss
of a family member.

00:52.139 --> 00:54.402
Perhaps we'd all like
to go around the room

00:54.445 --> 00:56.969
and each one of say something
that we liked

00:57.013 --> 00:59.015
- about Colin Robinson?
- Oh, leave us alone, Guillermo.

00:59.059 --> 01:00.538
You're giving everyone
a big bummer.

01:00.582 --> 01:02.192
When she's right, she's right.

01:02.236 --> 01:04.020
Should he even be here?
I know.

01:04.064 --> 01:07.502
I did think this was sort of
a "vampires only" portrait.

01:07.545 --> 01:09.199
Hey, he is a valued member
of the team

01:09.243 --> 01:12.115
and has every right
to be in this portrait.

01:12.159 --> 01:14.770
Even though he is a dog.

01:14.813 --> 01:16.250
I wasn't talking about the dog,
you halfwit,

01:16.293 --> 01:17.860
I was talking about Gizmo.

01:17.903 --> 01:18.948
Yes, well,
Gizmo needs to be here

01:18.991 --> 01:20.863
to help control the Hellhound.

01:20.906 --> 01:22.212
<i>If they talked about
their feelings,</i>

01:22.256 --> 01:23.605
<i>then the healing could begin.</i>

01:23.648 --> 01:24.780
- Guillermo,

01:24.823 --> 01:26.173
your Hellhound is
wandering around

01:26.216 --> 01:27.826
and pissing all over
our floors.

01:27.870 --> 01:30.133
<i>And once they're healed,
they would realize that</i>

01:30.177 --> 01:31.613
<i>the dynamic's a little off.</i>

01:31.656 --> 01:34.311
So maybe they need
to make a new vampire.

01:34.355 --> 01:37.575
I-I just heard it,
and I know...

01:37.619 --> 01:39.142
I know what you're thinking,

01:39.186 --> 01:41.405
but I truly believe that
that's what's needed

01:41.449 --> 01:44.713
to really restore--
And I deserve it.

01:46.932 --> 01:49.370
♪ <i>Don't sing if you want
to live long♪</i>

01:49.413 --> 01:52.721
♪ <i>They have no use
for your song♪</i>

01:52.764 --> 01:55.637
♪ <i>You're dead, you're dead,
you're dead♪</i>

01:55.680 --> 01:57.465
♪ <i>You're dead
