03:00.092 --> 03:02.791
<i>This was a gaffer
I worked with onER.</i>

03:02.834 --> 03:04.662
<i>The guy had just
such an amazing face,</i>

03:04.706 --> 03:06.229
<i>I was just staring at it.</i>

03:06.273 --> 03:07.926
I was staring at it
when I was on camera,

03:07.970 --> 03:09.754
which would get me in trouble,
you know?

03:09.798 --> 03:12.931
<i>But I think
I really got his essence.</i>

03:12.975 --> 03:14.585
So when the gang here said
that they needed

03:14.629 --> 03:16.239
a new portrait done,
I said I'd be more than happy

03:16.283 --> 03:18.894
to stick around and do it
because I had some downtime

03:18.937 --> 03:21.549
between the next meeting of
the Worldwide Vampiric Council

03:21.592 --> 03:25.335
and the two-episode arc
I booked on <i>SVU</i> next month.

03:25.379 --> 03:27.424
You gotta remember
I came up with MTV in the '90s,

03:27.468 --> 03:29.296
where they were like,
"Go shoot 15 hours

03:29.339 --> 03:30.862
"of <i>Jimmy the Cab Driver,</i>

03:30.906 --> 03:32.386
and then we'll figure out
where to stick it later,"

03:32.429 --> 03:34.039
- but when I got <i>Grounded...
Oof.</i>

03:34.083 --> 03:35.824
- This buhbutz is really
killing me.
- I know.

03:35.867 --> 03:38.261
Right? I mean,
I like the cinema,

03:38.305 --> 03:40.524
but don't need to know
how the sausage is made.

03:40.568 --> 03:42.309
Yeah, and it's kind of
insensitive.

03:42.352 --> 03:43.527
I mean, we're all still
mourning the death

03:43.571 --> 03:45.181
- of Colin Robinson.
- I'm not.

03:45.225 --> 03:46.226
Well, that's what
I'm talking about.

03:46.269 --> 03:47.749
We need to talk about that.

03:47.792 --> 03:48.532
- How you're feeling...
- We don't need to talk

03:48.576 --> 03:49.968
about anything.

03:50.012 --> 03:51.796
We are having our picture
painted.

03:51.840 --> 03:54.016
Then we will have a picture
that Colin Robinson is not in,

03:54.059 --> 03:55.583
and we can forget about him
forever,

03:55.626 --> 03:56.888
and this will heal us.

03:56.932 --> 03:58.890
Why did we have to rush it?

03:58.934 --> 04:00.196
The corpse has barely
begun to stink,

04:00.240 --> 04:01.719
and we've got the <i>Tao of Steve</i>

04:01.763 --> 04:03.286
- painting our portrait.
Oh, here we go.

04:03.330 --> 04:06.071
Nadja's masking her
true feelings with a joke.

04:06.115 --> 04:08.073
That was not a joke.
A joke has a punchline.

04:08.117 --> 04:09.553
And you wouldn't know
a punchline if it ran over

04:09.597 --> 04:11.251
your scrotum with
a penny farthing!

04:13.470 --> 04:16.299
Oh, I am sorry,
but that was a good one.

04:16.343 --> 04:19.171
Also, I feast upon hate.

04:19.215 --> 04:21.304
You know what?
Fuck this whole thing!

04:21.348 --> 04:24.351
Fuck you! Fuck you! Fuck you!

04:24.394 --> 04:27.963
You're cool.
Fuck you, and fuck you!

04:28.006 --> 04:29.486
- Fuck all this shit!
- Whoa.

04:29.530 --> 04:31.314
You are not storming away
from me.

04:31.358 --> 04:34.099
I am storming away from you,
but in a different direction!

04:34.143 --> 04:35.840
- Hey, whoa, whoa, whoa.
- Fuck you.

04:35.884 --> 04:37.189
You know what,
maybe we should just

04:37.233 --> 04:38.887
take five, shake it off.

04:38.930 --> 04:40.889
When he says "take five,"
five of what?

04:40.932 --> 04:42.412
And where are we taking them?

04:42.456 --> 04:45.415
This last year,
it has not been easy on me.

04:45.459 --> 04:47.765
<i>My search for love has</i>

04:47.809 --> 04:49.332
been stymied at every turn.

04:49.376 --> 04:51.073
- I'm a lesbian.
- Are you sure?

04:51.116 --> 04:52.248
Definitely sure.

04:52.292 --> 04:54.250
Would you do me the honor
of being

04:54.294 --> 04:55.686
my vampire bride?

04:55.730 --> 04:57.645
I was married before.

04:57.688 --> 04:59.951
<i>I discovered that
there is no meaning or purpose</i>

04:59.995 --> 05:01.823
<i>to the universe,</i>

05:01.866 --> 05:03.607
because of the Big Bang Theory.

05:03.651 --> 05:06.741
And on top of all that,
the death of Colin Robinson--

05:06.784 --> 05:10.440
it has, I must confess,
hit me quite hard.

05:10.484 --> 05:12.355
Life is precious.

05:12.399 --> 05:15.358
Even so-called eternal life
can be snuffed out

05:15.402 --> 05:17.055
at a moment's notice.

05:17.099 --> 05:19.841
Colin Robinson's head imploding
into a pile of goo

05:19.884 --> 05:24.628
has made me realize that I need
to make the most of my life.

05:24.672 --> 05:27.762
Which is why I've decided
to leave Staten Island

05:27.805 --> 05:29.764
- and travel the world.
- What?

05:29.807 --> 05:33.071
Visit the Great Fjords of
whatever country they're in.

05:33.115 --> 05:35.160
Get a job on one of those boats
that collect plastic

05:35.204 --> 05:36.945
- from the ocean.
- What the hell
are you talking about?

05:36.988 --> 05:40.905
- Guillermo, did I not tell you
all this already?
- No.

05:40.949 --> 05:42.777
- Sorry. Would you mind giving
us a moment?
- Sorry.

05:42.820 --> 05:44.344
Can you just give us
one minute?

05:44.387 --> 05:45.606
- Thank you so much.
Appreciate it.

05:45.649 --> 05:47.259
Careful with the rug.

05:47.303 --> 05:48.913
You can't make any rational
decisions right now

05:48.957 --> 05:50.437
because you're dealing
with Colin Robinson's death

05:50.480 --> 05:51.786
and you're running away
from your feelings.

05:51.829 --> 05:53.396
Yeah. So what?
I hate my feelings.

05:53.440 --> 05:55.137
You know what, this plan,
it sounds great out loud,

05:55.180 --> 05:56.921
but I-I, I just can't drop
everything that I'm doing.

05:56.965 --> 05:58.488
I have duties, you know.
Responsibilities.

05:58.532 --> 06:00.272
Like, my mom is here.
I can't just pack a bag

06:00.316 --> 06:01.665
and go on a world tour with you
at the drop of a hat.

06:01.709 --> 06:04.494
You're not coming with me.

06:04.538 --> 06:06.409
What?

06:06.453 --> 06:08.672
You are one of the things
I need to get away from

06:08.716 --> 06:10.326
to make a fresh start.

06:10.370 --> 06:12.502
No offense.

06:12.546 --> 06:14.330
Okay, well,
how you gonna travel?

06:14.374 --> 06:16.114
Just by night?
You're just gonna carry

06:16.158 --> 06:17.768
your ancestral dirt with you
and your coffin wherever you go?

06:17.812 --> 06:20.031
- That-that's insane.
- Yes, you're right.

06:20.075 --> 06:21.772
There's a lot of details
to figure out.

06:21.816 --> 06:24.862
And you are going
to figure them out for me.

06:24.906 --> 06:27.387
- Oh, surprise, surprise.
- As your last duty.

06:28.997 --> 06:31.956
My sweet, sweet Guillermo.

06:32.000 --> 06:35.177
You don't understand because?

06:35.220 --> 06:37.179
I'm not a vampire.

06:37.222 --> 06:39.616
Yes! Trust me,

06:39.660 --> 06:42.489
Nadja and Laszlo,
they are itching to get away.

06:42.532 --> 06:45.274
These vampire pods,
they don't last forever.

06:45.317 --> 06:47.450
And I'm not gonna be
the last one in here

06:47.494 --> 06:50.018
all alone like a fucking loser.

06:52.847 --> 06:54.501
I would rather not talk
about the death

06:54.544 --> 06:57.591
of Shmolin Shmobinson
because my dear husband Laszlo

06:57.634 --> 06:59.114
is having a bit of
a hard time dealing with it.

06:59.157 --> 07:00.594
What are you talking about?

07:00.637 --> 07:02.378
I said you were having
a hard time dealing

07:02.422 --> 07:04.859
with Colin Robinson's very
disgusting and tragic death.

07:04.902 --> 07:07.296
Well, that would be bullshit,
then, wouldn't it, my darling?

07:07.339 --> 07:09.037
I couldn't give a tinker's fig.

07:09.080 --> 07:10.473
- People die all the time.

07:10.517 --> 07:12.954
- Animals die, plants die.

07:12.997 --> 07:14.042
Oh, Gizmo, it's just you.

07:14.085 --> 07:15.783
