07:15.826 --> 07:18.002
Can't you see I'm doing my
talking-to-the-camera thing?

07:18.046 --> 07:20.614
I'm busy. Shoo!

07:20.657 --> 07:22.137
...by lunchtime I was
in the whorehouse

07:22.180 --> 07:24.487
with two prostitutes
and three good-time boys.

07:24.531 --> 07:27.229
Hold on, I've just had
the best idea.

07:27.272 --> 07:28.448
I think I might know
just the thing

07:28.491 --> 07:30.493
to cheer you up, my love.

07:30.537 --> 07:32.016
I don't need cheering up.

07:32.060 --> 07:33.801
How's about me and you
take a lovely little trip

07:33.844 --> 07:37.108
- back to merry old England?
- No.

07:37.152 --> 07:38.762
We could get a red bus
and make love in it.

07:38.806 --> 07:41.983
We could get a black cab
and make love in it.

07:42.026 --> 07:44.420
We could go to Madame Tussaud's
and look around.

07:44.464 --> 07:46.117
If I were to need
rest and recuperation

07:46.161 --> 07:49.120
for my dear friend's death,
that fuck hole would be

07:49.164 --> 07:51.035
the last place on Earth

07:51.079 --> 07:52.428
that I would choose
to go back to.

07:52.472 --> 07:54.909
You know this.
I made a precious vow

07:54.952 --> 07:58.129
- never to go back there again.
- Laszlo! Ugh!

07:58.173 --> 08:01.350
United Kingdom?
United Ding-dong, more like.

08:01.393 --> 08:03.961
Nadja, Nadja,
I really need your help.

08:04.005 --> 08:05.397
It's about Nandor.

08:07.008 --> 08:10.881
- I suppose we just wait.
I don't know.

08:10.925 --> 08:12.404
We have a problem.

08:12.448 --> 08:13.928
You are not the only one
with problems, Gizmo!

08:13.971 --> 08:15.843
Look at you.
"Oh, everyone feel sorry for me

08:15.886 --> 08:17.322
"'cause I'm a pathetic human,

08:17.366 --> 08:18.846
"and I can't fly,
and all I do is

08:18.889 --> 08:20.456
sit on the toilet all day."

08:20.500 --> 08:23.590
Well, what about my needs?
Look. Look at this.

08:26.549 --> 08:28.899
Uh, that's not how that works.

08:28.943 --> 08:30.422
- Oh, you do it!
- Okay.

08:30.466 --> 08:32.512
This is a glass paperweight,

08:32.555 --> 08:35.123
and this is the TV control.

08:35.166 --> 08:37.081
- We push this in...
- Patronizing.

08:37.125 --> 08:38.692
...and play.

08:41.956 --> 08:45.089
<i>-This is not taping over
RuPaul, is it?
- No, no.</i>

08:45.133 --> 08:46.830
<i>-'Cause I haven't seen
the latest episode.
- It's a fresh...</i>

08:46.874 --> 08:49.180
<i>-Okay, good. What?
- We're recording.</i>

08:49.224 --> 08:50.747
<i>Oh. Ahem.</i>

08:50.791 --> 08:54.272
<i>Dark greetings,
Nadja of Antipaxos.</i>

08:54.316 --> 08:56.710
<i>You must know by now
that I've had my eye on you</i>

08:56.753 --> 08:58.363
<i>for quite some time.</i>

08:58.407 --> 09:00.975
<i>Your work on your local
Vampiric Council</i>

09:01.018 --> 09:03.891
<i>has been quite impressive.
Yas, queen.</i>

09:03.934 --> 09:06.023
<i>Everyone is going on about it.</i>

09:06.067 --> 09:09.461
<i>And thus, we would be delighted
for you to join us</i>

09:09.505 --> 09:11.681
<i>in London, in England,</i>

09:11.725 --> 09:14.162
<i>where you will take a position
that ranks amongst</i>

09:14.205 --> 09:18.427
<i>the highest of all worldwide
Vampiric Council positions.</i>

09:18.470 --> 09:20.690
<i>We do hope you'll accept
this offer promptly,</i>

09:20.734 --> 09:22.736
<i>because as you know,
vampires hate waiting.</i>

09:22.779 --> 09:26.087
<i>Even though we're immortal,
waiting is just still a thing.</i>

09:26.130 --> 09:29.003
<i>So, if you accept,
as fast as you can,</i>

09:29.046 --> 09:32.528
<i>tape your acceptance speech
on a VHS tape, and then</i>

09:32.572 --> 09:35.575
<i>put it in an envelope
and send it by mail,</i>

09:35.618 --> 09:37.794
<i>and eventually
it'll get to us.</i>

09:37.838 --> 09:39.579
<i>This is your last ch...</i>

09:39.622 --> 09:41.624
You're thinking of leaving, too?

09:41.668 --> 09:43.583
Of course I want to leave.

09:43.626 --> 09:45.846
It is such a great honor
and opportunity,

09:45.889 --> 09:48.065
and I would have a chance
to finally do something

09:48.109 --> 09:49.763
with my stupid eternal life.

09:49.806 --> 09:51.199
But it is not to be.

09:51.242 --> 09:52.417
- Good.
- What?!

09:52.461 --> 09:53.897
I mean, uh, why?

09:53.941 --> 09:56.204
Because Laszlo will never
go back to England.

09:56.247 --> 09:58.249
You heard him.
He has sworn it.

09:58.293 --> 10:00.121
But I cannot leave him
on his own.

10:00.164 --> 10:03.646
You know, I went on holiday
for two weeks in 1924,

10:03.690 --> 10:05.692
and when I got back,
he hadn't fed himself once.

10:05.735 --> 10:08.956
He spent all his time writing
poetry and wanking.

10:08.999 --> 10:10.522
So, no, I can't go.

10:10.566 --> 10:12.873
So you're saying
if Laszlo doesn't go,

10:12.916 --> 10:15.789
then you certainly won't go?

10:15.832 --> 10:18.008
I literally just
said that to you.

10:20.532 --> 10:22.012
I know it seems like
I'm panicking,

10:22.056 --> 10:23.840
but I'm not panicking.
It's just that I'm afraid

10:23.884 --> 10:25.668
it's like a party; as soon as
one person leaves the party,

10:25.712 --> 10:27.496
another person decides it's okay
for them to leave the party,

10:27.539 --> 10:28.758
and before you know it,
the whole party's over.

10:28.802 --> 10:29.803
