of your life

10:29.846 --> 10:31.108
to a certain type of party,

10:31.152 --> 10:31.892
and it's not gonna end
like this!

10:34.851 --> 10:36.723
- Sorry.

10:36.766 --> 10:38.115
Hey...

10:38.159 --> 10:39.290
Sorry, I didn't mean
to startle you,

10:39.334 --> 10:40.814
I just had a question.

10:40.857 --> 10:42.729
If this has anything to do
with the fact that

10:42.772 --> 10:44.731
I won't let anybody touch
Colin Robinson's body,

10:44.774 --> 10:47.298
yet I myself have not been
down to the basement

10:47.342 --> 10:49.823
to pay my respects,
I can answer that.

10:49.866 --> 10:52.782
There's nothing down there.
Only a bag of skin.

10:52.826 --> 10:56.264
Plus I find that kind of
sentimental gesture

10:56.307 --> 10:57.613
fucking tawdry.

10:57.657 --> 11:01.486
No, no, that wasn't it.
I wasn't--

11:01.530 --> 11:04.011
No, it was just a random
question that I was--

11:04.054 --> 11:07.754
What do you think about England?
Is it a cool place to live?

11:07.797 --> 11:11.888
No, it is absolutely not
a cool place to live.

11:11.932 --> 11:13.760
- Why not?
- You want to know a story about

11:13.803 --> 11:17.067
- England and the English way?
- Yeah.

11:17.111 --> 11:20.680
- I used to be a member
of a club.

11:20.723 --> 11:22.203
The Sherwood Club of London.

11:22.246 --> 11:24.596
My father was a member of a club

11:24.640 --> 11:26.947
called the Sherwood Club
of London.

11:26.990 --> 11:28.557
His father was a member
of a club

11:28.600 --> 11:31.429
called the Sherwood Club
of London.

11:31.473 --> 11:34.084
- You get where I'm going
with this?
- I think so.

11:34.128 --> 11:36.521
Anyway, treachery was afoot,
and I was expelled

11:36.565 --> 11:38.741
from the Sherwood Club
of London.

11:38.785 --> 11:41.875
The decision was unanimous.

11:41.918 --> 11:46.053
So I left the UK and came here,

11:46.096 --> 11:47.489
to the New World.

11:47.532 --> 11:49.926
To the land of opportunity,

11:49.970 --> 11:52.799
where men--
and, I'm told, some women--

11:52.842 --> 11:55.453
can be kings
of their own castle.

11:55.497 --> 11:59.022
Where industrialists can rub
shoulders with chimney sweeps.

11:59.066 --> 12:01.285
My late friend Walt Whitman
said to me,

12:01.329 --> 12:04.071
-"You'd better put
that away, Laszlo..."
- So you're saying

12:04.114 --> 12:08.423
you would never, ever
go back to England.

12:08.466 --> 12:09.772
Yes, I am.

12:09.816 --> 12:11.469
- I would never, ever,

12:11.513 --> 12:14.342
ever, ever, ever

12:14.385 --> 12:15.735
go back to England.

12:15.778 --> 12:17.127
Well, there you have it.

12:17.171 --> 12:18.738
- Oh.

12:18.781 --> 12:19.826
- There's the bell.
Five minutes, vamps.

12:19.869 --> 12:20.783
Time to get back
to the portrait.

12:20.827 --> 12:22.567
Tell him to fuck off.

12:22.611 --> 12:23.960
- I'm busy here.
- All right.

12:24.004 --> 12:26.223
Plus, that conversation
about my homeland

12:26.267 --> 12:27.964
has given me the pip.

12:28.008 --> 12:29.879
- Of course.
- I shall need ten minutes
to recover.

12:38.670 --> 12:40.455
Hel-lo.

12:40.498 --> 12:42.762
Your English is
coming along nicely.

12:42.805 --> 12:44.981
- Hey, guys.
- Hey.
Hey...

12:45.025 --> 12:46.591
You see?
You have made progress.

12:46.635 --> 12:49.072
I have to remind myself
that vampires always make

12:49.116 --> 12:51.858
these grandiose plans,
but they never see them through.

12:51.901 --> 12:53.685
- Everything's gonna be A-ok...
It's a map.

12:53.729 --> 12:55.209
It's a cape.

12:55.252 --> 12:57.080
- It's a mape!
I'll tell you what,

12:57.124 --> 13:00.170
- world travel looks good
on you, Nandor.
- Thank you.

13:00.214 --> 13:03.260
- Oh, hi, Guillermo. Good news.

13:03.304 --> 13:06.437
She is an expert on
international vampire travel.

13:06.481 --> 13:09.919
It's true. I book all the trips
for the Vampiric Council.

13:09.963 --> 13:12.356
- Really the only fun part
of my job.
- Yes.

13:12.400 --> 13:14.097
Anyway, we figured out
all the details

13:14.141 --> 13:15.838
- so you don't have to
worry about a thing.
- No.

13:15.882 --> 13:18.319
I mean, I don't think
you've thought of everything.

13:18.362 --> 13:19.886
- I mean, what about...
- The coffin? Super easy.

13:19.929 --> 13:21.409
All you need is international
bill of lading,

13:21.452 --> 13:22.627
- and that's kind of it.
- Really?

13:22.671 --> 13:24.064
Here's a tip.
- Yes?

13:24.107 --> 13:26.936
Put your ancestral soil
in your Jansport

13:26.980 --> 13:30.070
so it's always on your back, and
you can just lie down anywhere.

13:30.113 --> 13:32.507
- What's a Jansport?
- It's a backpack.
- It's a backpack.

13:32.550 --> 13:35.379
- It's a very popular backpack.
- It's a children's backpack.

13:35.423 --> 13:37.251
That's smart.
That's very smart.

13:37.294 --> 13:38.861
- Anyone could have
thought of that.
Let's celebrate.

13:41.908 --> 13:43.170
Master, listen to me.

13:43.213 --> 13:44.911
Nadja and Laszlo
aren't leaving after all.

13:44.954 --> 13:46.869
So you don't have to worry
about being all by yourself.

13:46.913 --> 13:49.263
But I'm excited
for this trip now.

13:49.306 --> 13:52.396
It's gonna be a real eat,
prey, love kind journey for me.

13:52.440 --> 13:54.616
What do you mean?
You're gonna pray?

13:54.659 --> 13:56.705
Well, how am I gonna eat if
I don't prey on people, dummy?

13:56.748 --> 14:00.535
Now, you must travel
by railway and always at night.

14:00.578 --> 14:01.971
It's the only way
to stay safe.

14:02.015 --> 14:04.452
Plus, it's usually much cheaper.

14:04.495 --> 14:06.541
Oh, I'm so excited.

14:06.584 --> 14:09.544
I cannot wait to see
all the wonders of the world.

14:09.587 --> 14:11.154
The Colossus of Rhodes.

14:11.198 --> 14:13.591
The Hanging Gardens
of Babylon.

14:13.635 --> 14:15.550
The beautiful unmarred face
of the Sphinx.

14:15.593 --> 14:17.900
Ah, cheers to that!

14:17.944 --> 14:19.293
- We should finish our portrait.
Come on, everybody!

14:19.336 --> 14:20.294
- Shall we?
- Absolutely.

14:20.337 --> 14:21.469
And there are so many

14:21.512 --> 14:23.036
wonderful vampire hosts

14:23.079 --> 14:24.515
- I can hook you up with.
- Oh, please.

14:26.517 --> 14:27.997
You know, you spend
your whole life wanting

14:28.041 --> 14:30.695
to shoot in New York;
Brooklyn in this case.

14:30.739 --> 14:32.262
We were at Steiner Studios.

14:32.306 --> 14:34.656
And then you find yourself
so far from your family,

14:34.699 --> 14:36.745
- it gets kind of lonely.
- I have to say something.

14:36.788 --> 14:39.226
- I'm sorry, Donal Logue.
- Quite all right.

14:39.269 --> 14:41.750
I know that we're all
a little bit shaken up

14:41.793 --> 14:43.795
- by the death of Colin Robinson.
Speak for yourself.

14:43.839 --> 14:45.885
I'm as dry as a nun's doodah.

14:45.928 --> 14:47.756
Well, regardless,
we have to remember

14:47.799 --> 14:50.019
that there's the family
that you're born into,

14:50.063 --> 14:51.760
and then there's
your chosen family.

14:51.803 --> 14:53.501
That's what we are.

14:53.544 --> 14:56.112
We're a chosen family,
and it's a rare thing...

14:56.156 --> 14:57.505
I've been offered
a job in England,

14:57.548 --> 14:58.810
- and I want to move there!
- Whoo-hoo!

14:58.854 --> 15:00.290
- Over my dead body.

15:00.334 --> 15:02.031
Well, it seems everyone's
getting into it now.

15:02.075 --> 15:05.121
I have decided to leave
the island of Staten,

15:05.165 --> 15:09.473
travel the world and
rediscover my groove.

15:09.517 --> 15:11.301
- You are so selfish, Laszlo!
She's right.

15:11.345 --> 15:14.609
I made a vow never to return
to that cack house

15:14.652 --> 15:16.089
ever, ever again.

15:16.132 --> 15:18.308
- But why?
- You know why.

15:18.352 --> 15:21.790
- The British are a pack of
classist wankers.
Here, here.

15:21.833 --> 15:24.271
And those fuckers
expelled me

15:24.314 --> 15:25.837
- from the Sherwood...
- From the Sherwood Club.

15:25.881 --> 15:27.752
Yes, I know. You have told me
so many times.

15:27.796 --> 15:29.363
Yeah, I've told you
so many times,

15:29.406 --> 15:31.713
but I've never told you why.

15:31.756 --> 15:33.454
And now I will.

15:33.497 --> 15:34.890
I always thought
it was because of

15:34.934 --> 15:35.978
all the whores and the whoring.

15:36.022 --> 15:37.110
They don't give a fuck about

15:37.153 --> 15:38.676
whores and whoring, my darling.

15:38.720 --> 15:40.765
They didn't even care
that I was a vampire.

15:40.809 --> 15:43.986
What they did object to,
however, was the fact

15:44.030 --> 15:46.249
that I fell in love
and eventually married

15:46.293 --> 15:50.601
the most beautiful,
simple girl.

15:50.645 --> 15:53.517
A girl with no surname,

15:53.561 --> 15:56.477
no social standing.

15:56.520 --> 15:59.262
They actually called her
a peasant girl.

15:59.306 --> 16:04.050
A girl from a tiny village
on a dirt island

16:04.093 --> 16:05.442
in the Mediterranean.

16:05.486 --> 16:08.968
That girl is the most
beautiful girl

16:09.011 --> 16:10.578
I have ever known.

16:10.621 --> 16:14.277
That girl's name--
yes, my darling--

16:14.321 --> 16:18.064
- Is my name?
- Is your name. Nadja.

16:18.107 --> 16:21.110
- Oh, snap.
- Snap, indeed, Donal.

16:21.154 --> 16:23.808
But, my dark baby,

16:23.852 --> 16:26.115
I will be returning to England
to assume a position

16:26.159 --> 16:28.596
on the Supreme Vampiric Council.

16:28.639 --> 16:30.119
Wait, what?

16:30.163 --> 16:32.556
We would be going back
as the tip of the tops

16:32.600 --> 16:33.862
of the upper classes.

16:33.905 --> 16:35.516
- Really?
- Yeah.

16:35.559 --> 16:38.649
Well, that changes pretty much
fucking everything.

16:38.693 --> 16:41.609
- Count me in.
No, no, Laszlo,

16:41.652 --> 16:43.741
You made a lifelong vow
to never go back

16:43.785 --> 16:45.830
- to that shithole, remember?
- Didn't you hear what
she just said?

16:45.874 --> 16:47.658
We're gonna rule
the fucking place.

16:47.702 --> 16:49.138
Rule Britannia!

16:52.794 --> 16:54.926
- Oh, okay, yeah. Oh, yeah.
- Now I'm ready.

16:54.970 --> 16:56.537
Now I am ready.

16:56.580 --> 16:58.713
- So romantic. Great!
Oh, yeah, get some.

16:58.756 --> 17:02.021
It is decided, we will all
move on from this place

17:02.064 --> 17:03.848
- and regroup elsewhere.
- Yes. Whoo-hoo!

17:03.892 --> 17:06.199
I think we should all
just take a second, breathe.

17:06.242 --> 17:08.331
You know,
just take a deep breath.

17:08.375 --> 17:10.072
And, I mean, the portrait's
not even done, so we could...

17:10.116 --> 17:11.682
No, it's almost done.
- What?

17:11.726 --> 17:13.032
And that's that.

17:13.075 --> 17:15.077
So, you're all free
to go about doing

17:15.121 --> 17:16.600
whatever the hell it was
you were doing before.

17:16.644 --> 17:18.907
Plus, I just got a text
from my agent

17:18.950 --> 17:21.562
that I have to do a self-tape
for a CBS pilot,

17:21.605 --> 17:22.867
so Logue out.

17:25.218 --> 17:28.047
Always a drama with
this little rascal.

17:29.048 --> 17:30.353
I will fix.

17:30.397 --> 17:33.095
You know, usually when
someone is upset,

17:33.139 --> 17:34.705
they go to their own room,

17:34.749 --> 17:37.186
but I understand why
you would come to my room,

17:37.230 --> 17:39.101
as it is a far superior
room to yours.

17:39.145 --> 17:41.016
Which probably makes you feel
even more depressed.

17:41.060 --> 17:43.888
- Is this your attempt
at cheering me up?
- Guillermo...

17:43.932 --> 17:47.544
You want us to go through this
one more time? Hmm?

17:47.588 --> 17:49.329
It is a very dangerous world
out there.

17:49.372 --> 17:52.114
You're joking, right? It's me
who's been protecting you!

17:52.158 --> 17:54.029
So what, you shooed away some
assassins; who gives a shit?

17:54.073 --> 17:55.683
If it wasn't for me,
you would be dead by now.

17:55.726 --> 17:58.120
If not by assassins
then by my very own hands

17:58.164 --> 17:59.861
because I am,
and I will remind you,

17:59.904 --> 18:02.733
by birth and lineage,
a vampire killer.

18:02.777 --> 18:06.172
And the only reason
you're alive is because...

18:06.215 --> 18:07.956
I let you live.

18:11.438 --> 18:14.049
What did you just say?

18:14.093 --> 18:18.053
I said, the only reason
you're alive

18:18.097 --> 18:20.142
is because I

18:20.186 --> 18:24.581
let you live.

18:27.149 --> 18:29.934
My poor, dear thing.

18:29.978 --> 18:32.111
You forgot that
we hypnotized you

18:32.154 --> 18:34.896
to make it physically impossible
for you to harm me

18:34.939 --> 18:36.724
or any or your masters.

18:36.767 --> 18:38.247
Do you remember that? Hmm?

18:38.291 --> 18:41.598
No, because we used hypnosis.

18:41.642 --> 18:43.339
Hypnosis doesn't work on me.

18:43.383 --> 18:45.907
I just let you think it did
so you wouldn't feel weak.

18:45.950 --> 18:48.910
I never feel weak,
my furry little friend!

18:53.306 --> 18:56.135
No, no.
No, no, no, no, no, no.

18:56.178 --> 18:57.397
Master, your-your sword
needs polishing.

18:57.440 --> 18:58.963
It does?

18:59.007 --> 19:01.270
- Hey!

19:02.228 --> 19:05.187
- Plancha!
- Don't you dare!

19:05.231 --> 19:06.971
Ow.

19:10.018 --> 19:12.412
Once a familiar,
always a familiar!

19:19.201 --> 19:20.333
Uh-uh-uh.

19:22.378 --> 19:25.120
You almost hit John!

19:29.298 --> 19:31.518
Yes, yes, finally.

19:31.561 --> 19:33.172
This is what
I've been waiting for.

19:33.215 --> 19:35.913
- What?
- Put the crucifix away,
Guillermo.

19:35.957 --> 19:37.611
You have passed the test.

19:39.308 --> 19:41.136
What test?

19:41.180 --> 19:44.183
I have been worried that you
have been going a little soft.

19:44.226 --> 19:47.795
But tonight, you have
proved to me finally

19:47.838 --> 19:50.711
that you can take care
of yourself.

19:50.754 --> 19:52.713
And more importantly,

19:52.756 --> 19:55.672
you can take care of me.

19:55.716 --> 19:58.066
Guillermo de la Cruz,

19:58.109 --> 20:02.897
will you do me the honor...

20:02.940 --> 20:06.379
of accompanying me on my journey
around the world?

20:06.422 --> 20:09.469
If you're scared of me
right now...

20:09.512 --> 20:11.732
If you accompany me
on this journey,

20:11.775 --> 20:15.736
when we arrive at the banks
of the River Tigris

20:15.779 --> 20:18.521
in my homeland of Al-Qolnadar,

20:18.565 --> 20:21.263
you will take a knee,

20:21.307 --> 20:23.918
and I will make you...

20:23.961 --> 20:26.225
a vampire.

20:27.269 --> 20:29.576
- Really?
- My word

20:29.619 --> 20:31.447
is my bond.

20:32.796 --> 20:36.365
Then yes. Yes, of course
I'll go with you, Master.

20:37.366 --> 20:39.890
There will be plenty of time
for that kind of thing.

20:39.934 --> 20:42.328
- Right.
- Well...

20:42.371 --> 20:44.678
you should go,
start making arrangements.

20:44.721 --> 20:45.896
Yes.

20:45.940 --> 20:48.769
Let our great journey commence!

20:49.944 --> 20:52.338
That little fucker can
really move when he wants to.

20:55.906 --> 20:57.995
Yeah, I'm gonna miss
this house, but...

20:58.039 --> 21:00.259
definitely won't miss
cleaning it.

21:00.302 --> 21:03.436
It'll be sad to say bye
to Nadja and Laszlo.

21:03.479 --> 21:05.264
They're off
on a big adventure now,

21:05.307 --> 21:07.048
so I'm really happy for them.

21:07.091 --> 21:09.311
Don't you even fucking dare!

21:09.355 --> 21:12.183
But the real thing
I'm looking forward to is...

21:12.227 --> 21:16.362
traveling the whole world
with my Nand-- master.

21:17.624 --> 21:19.147
<i>Just the two of us.</i>

21:20.540 --> 21:22.106
- Master.
- Yes?

21:22.150 --> 21:24.108
You need to hurry up.
I still have to help

21:24.152 --> 21:26.110
Nadja and Laszlo load
their coffin into the boat.

21:26.154 --> 21:28.765
And then you and I are catching
a midnight train.

21:28.809 --> 21:32.073
Why are you helping them when my
ancestral soil needs scooping?

21:32.116 --> 21:33.596
Because it's the last time
I can say goodbye to them.

21:33.640 --> 21:35.859
- I thought you'd understand.
- Oh, Guillermo.

21:35.903 --> 21:37.818
Fine, I will allow it.

21:37.861 --> 21:39.907
But don't think for one second
I'll be getting into the habit

21:39.950 --> 21:41.909
- of scooping my own soil.
- No, of course not.

21:41.952 --> 21:43.650
Oh. Can you take my luggage
to the train station?

21:43.693 --> 21:45.216
I don't want to carry it
to the dock

21:45.260 --> 21:46.479
and then have
to carry it back...

21:46.522 --> 21:48.698
Hey! What,
am I working for you now?

21:50.265 --> 21:51.353
I'm kidding, Guillermo.

21:51.397 --> 21:52.833
I will take your bag for you.

21:52.876 --> 21:54.661
Okay, gracias.

21:54.704 --> 21:57.446
- Knock, knock,
Mr. Relentless.
- Hi.

21:57.490 --> 22:00.406
Hello.
I just wanted to say goodbye.

22:00.449 --> 22:03.713
- Thank you.
- I got you a little card.

22:03.757 --> 22:05.367
"Bon voyage."

22:05.411 --> 22:07.151
Those are
the wraiths' signatures.

22:07.195 --> 22:09.197
- Oh.
- Some of them
don't know how to write,

22:09.240 --> 22:11.634
and others once did
but have long since forgotten,

22:11.678 --> 22:13.636
so I just dipped
their claws in ink

22:13.680 --> 22:15.159
and let them go at it.

22:15.203 --> 22:16.944
Smart.

22:16.987 --> 22:18.119
Thank you.

22:18.162 --> 22:20.121
Should we hug now, or...?

22:20.164 --> 22:22.558
I think it would be too much.

22:22.602 --> 22:24.865
- Okay.
- Nandor, I have come
to bid you adieu.

22:24.908 --> 22:27.128
You are a vampire
I have known for a while now,

22:27.171 --> 22:29.348
and now our time together
has ended.

22:29.391 --> 22:30.697
Cheers! Bye! Ha!

22:30.740 --> 22:32.916
Nadja, Laszlo, <i>vámonos!</i>

22:32.960 --> 22:34.353
We have to go!

22:34.396 --> 22:35.658
Don't you dare shout at me,
Guillermo!

22:35.702 --> 22:37.181
I could suck out
all of your bodily fluids

22:37.225 --> 22:38.357
in less than two seconds.

22:39.532 --> 22:41.316
- Not gonna miss that.
- Laszlo?

22:41.360 --> 22:42.665
Where are you?
It's time to get to...

22:42.709 --> 22:44.754
Oh.

22:44.798 --> 22:46.930
What were you doing
in the basement, my dear?

22:46.974 --> 22:49.672
Nothing. Just taking care
of some business.

22:49.716 --> 22:52.066
Oh, my sweet love.

22:52.109 --> 22:54.068
Were you finally saying goodbye
to the decaying corpse

22:54.111 --> 22:55.852
of your very dead friend
Colin Robinson?

22:55.896 --> 22:57.376
Something like that.

22:57.419 --> 22:58.812
Are you okay?
Do you need a bit more time?

22:58.855 --> 23:00.248
Not at all. I feel fine.

23:00.291 --> 23:01.684
Let's rock and roll.

23:01.728 --> 23:03.904
We're missing
three boxes of porn.

23:13.870 --> 23:15.916
- Whoo-hoo! Guillermo, my things.

23:15.959 --> 23:18.484
- Coming.
- Ah, smell the sea.

23:18.527 --> 23:20.486
I do love a journey.

23:20.529 --> 23:22.879
- And I went ahead and downloaded

23:22.923 --> 23:24.751
all the seasons
of <i>RuPaul's Drag Race.</i>

23:24.794 --> 23:26.535
Thank you very much, Guillermo.

23:26.579 --> 23:28.929
It has been... nice.

23:28.972 --> 23:30.496
Yeah.

23:30.539 --> 23:32.715
My darling, I will see you

23:32.759 --> 23:35.631
when we are kissing the ground
of your native land

23:35.675 --> 23:38.591
and make love on the bones
of those who scorned you.

23:38.634 --> 23:40.636
Safe passage, my darling.

23:42.333 --> 23:45.685
- Are you in?
- Yes. Lock me up.

23:45.728 --> 23:48.165
Right. Now, come on,
don't fuck about, get that in.

23:48.209 --> 23:51.168
Why do you have water and food
if you can't even eat it?

23:51.212 --> 23:52.953
It's Oreos and Pedialyte.

23:52.996 --> 23:55.129
This stuff's worth its weight
in gold where I come from.

23:55.172 --> 23:57.044
I can barter that
and get anything I want.

23:57.087 --> 23:59.350
Makes sense. Well, this is it.

23:59.394 --> 24:01.396
- Indeed.
- All right.

24:01.440 --> 24:02.658
- Yeah.
- Okay.

24:02.702 --> 24:03.833
Right.

24:03.877 --> 24:05.400
Safe fare.

24:05.444 --> 24:06.706
You, too.

24:06.749 --> 24:08.447
It's a lot of Oreos.

24:08.490 --> 24:09.796
Make sure
you look after my wife.

24:09.839 --> 24:12.581
What? Aah! No! No, no, no, no!

24:12.625 --> 24:14.583
- No, no, no!

24:14.627 --> 24:16.672
What the fuck?! Master!

24:16.716 --> 24:17.934
Wait for me!

24:20.110 --> 24:23.287
Help! Let me out!
Let me out, Laszlo!

24:23.331 --> 24:25.812
Laszlo, please don't!
Hello! Hello?

24:26.813 --> 24:28.771
Hey...

24:31.339 --> 24:33.472
All aboard!

24:34.821 --> 24:37.345
Guillermo...!

24:38.738 --> 24:40.174
